ereducationin2020.HeisaseniormemberofIEEE.\nversity in 2020, and the M.Eng. degree from Duke\nUniversity in 2022. He worked as a research as-\nsistant in speech processing at Speech and Multi-\nmodal Intelligent Information Processing (SMIIP)\nLab in 2023. He is currently pursuing the Ph.D.\ndegree in the School of Computer Science under\nthe joint supervision of Prof. Juan Liu and Prof.\nMing Li. His research interests include anomalous\nsounddetection,generalaudioprocessingandaudio\nunderstanding.\nJuanLiu(SeniorMember,IEEE)receivedthePh.D.\ndegreeincomputerscienceandtheoryfromWuhan\nUniversityin1996.SheiscurrentlyaProfessorand\nDoctoral Supervisor with the School of Computer\nScience, Wuhan University, where she also serves\nas the Director of the Institute of Artificial Intelli-\ngence.Herresearchinterestsincludebioinformatics,\nmachine learning, data mining, pattern recognition,\nmedicalimageprocessing,andartificialintelligence\nmethods for speech, audio, and signal processing.\nShe has published more than 150 research papers\nandholdsorhasappliedformultiplenationalinventionpatentsandsoftware\ncopyrights.\n", "numLines": 621, "startLine": 1, "totalLines": 621}}}
