{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-9f69e7464a1c4db9", "type": "tool_result", "content": "[]\n===\n[]\n===\n[{\"paper\": {\"arxiv_id\": \"2509.09174\", \"title\": \"EchoX: Towards Mitigating Acoustic-Semantic Gap via Echo Training for Speech-to-Speech LLMs\", \"authors\": [\"Yuhao Zhang\", \"Yuhao Du\", \"Zhanchen Dai\", \"Xiangnan Ma\", \"Kaiqi Kou\", \"Benyou Wang\", \"Haizhou Li\"], \"year\": 2025, \"venue\": \"\", \"categories\": [\"cs.CL\", \"cs.AI\", \"cs.SD\"], \"topic\": \"audio_understanding\", \"tags\": [\"LALM\", \"LALM/\\u5bf9\\u8bdd\\u578b\", \"LALM/\\u97f3\\u9891\\u6807\\u8bb0-\\u878d\\u5408\", \"TTS\"], \"contributions\": [\"Identification of the acoustic-semantic gap as a primary cause of intelligence degradation in speech-to-speech large language models.\", \"Proposal of EchoX, a framework that uses an auxiliary Echo decoder to dynamically generate speech training targets based on semantic understanding.\", \"Introduction of a three-stage training pipeline consisting of speech-to-text training, text-to-codec training, and echo training to bridge the acoustic-semantic gap.\", \"Design of a denoising adapter combined with a cosine similarity loss to align hidden representations with text embeddings and minimize noise during speech token generation.\", \"Adoption of unit language to construct speech tokens that significantly compress speech sequences while maintaining synthesis quality.\", \"Development of a streaming inference mechanism based on a trigger feature to enable real-time generation and mitigate long-sequence generation difficulties.\", \"Demonstration of advanced performance on knowledge-based QA benchmarks using approximately six thousand hours of training data, achieving results comparable to models trained on millions of hours.\"], \"citations\": [{\"paper_id\": \"2409.00750\", \"title\": \"LibriSpeech\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"ASR dataset used for training the S2T module.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"HuBERT\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Used to extract continuous representations from the 11th hidden layer for unit extraction\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Soundwave\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Used as the audio encoding and adaptation architecture for the S2T LLM\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"LLaMA 3.2\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Base text LLM used for the 3B model\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"LLaMA 3.1\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Base text LLM used for the 8B model\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MLS\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Subset used as ASR training data (723k utterances, 3000 hours)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"AudioQA-1M\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"TTS training data (178k utterances, 989 hours, text only used)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"SpeechInstruct\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"TTS training data (31k utterances, 84 hours)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"HH-RLHF-Speech\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"TTS training data (124k utterances, 656 hours, converted from text)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"sharechatx\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"SQA training data (43k utterances, 178 hours)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Magpie-Pro-Speech+\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"SQA training data (117k utterances, 327 hours)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Google TTS\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Used in the data cleaning pipeline to synthesize speech\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"GPT-SoVITS\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Used in the data cleaning pipeline to synthesize speech\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Llama Questions\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Knowledge QA benchmark for evaluating semantic and knowledge reasoning ability\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Web Questions\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Knowledge QA benchmark for evaluating semantic and knowledge reasoning ability\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"TriviaQA\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Knowledge QA benchmark for evaluating semantic and knowledge reasoning ability\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"UTMOS\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Metric for evaluating the acoustic quality of generated speech\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"AlpacaEval\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Dataset used for human evaluation of speech interaction\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"OmniDRCA(2B)\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Evaluated 3B-level baseline model\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"LLaMA-Omni2-3B\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Evaluated 3B-level baseline model\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"GPT-4o-Realtime\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Evaluated 8B+ level baseline model\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"VITA-Audio\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Evaluated 8B+ level baseline model\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MinMo\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Evaluated 8B+ level baseline model\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MiniCPM-o 2.6\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Evaluated 8B+ level baseline model\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"OmniDRCA(8B)\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Evaluated 8B+ level baseline model\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"GLM-4-Voice\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Evaluated 8B+ level baseline model\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"LLaMA-Omni2-7B\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Evaluated 8B+ level baseline model\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Freeze-Omni\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Evaluated 8B+ level baseline model and human evaluation comparison target\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Moshi\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Evaluated 8B+ level baseline model\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}], \"code_url\": \"\", \"abstract\": \"Speech-to-speech large language models (SLLMs) are attracting increasing attention. Derived from text-based large language models (LLMs), SLLMs often exhibit degradation in knowledge and reasoning capabilities. We hypothesize that this limitation arises because current training paradigms for SLLMs fail to bridge the acoustic-semantic gap in the feature representation space. To address this issue, we propose EchoX, which leverages semantic representations and dynamically generates speech training targets. This approach integrates both acoustic and semantic learning, enabling EchoX to preserve strong reasoning abilities as a speech LLM. Experimental results demonstrate that EchoX, with about six thousand hours of training data, achieves advanced performance on multiple knowledge-based question-answering benchmarks. The project is available at https://github.com/FreedomIntelligence/EchoX.\", \"status\": \"unread\", \"compile_status\": \"compiled\", \"compiled_at\": \"2026-04-27T05:29:25.143825\"}, \"score\": 31}, {\"paper\": {\"arxiv_id\": \"2402.01912\", \"title\": \"Natural language guidance of high-fidelity text-to-speech with synthetic annotations\", \"authors\": [\"Dan Lyth\", \"Simon King\"], \"year\": 2024, \"venue\": \"\", \"categories\": [\"cs.SD\", \"cs.CL\", \"eess.AS\"], \"topic\": \"tts_vc\", \"tags\": [\"TTS\", \"TTS/\\u67b6\\u6784-AR-LLM\", \"TTS/\\u63a7\\u5236-NL\\u63cf\\u8ff0\", \"TTS/\\u529f\\u80fd-\\u591a\\u8bf4\\u8bdd\\u4eba\"], \"contributions\": [\"Proposed a scalable method for automatically labeling large speech datasets with multiple attributes including gender, accent, speaking rate, pitch, and recording conditions.\", \"Trained a speech language model on a 45k hour automatically-labeled dataset to independently control various speech attributes and create unseen speaker identity and style combinations via natural language.\", \"Demonstrated that high-fidelity audio generation can be achieved by training on a dataset with as little as 1% high-quality audio combined with state-of-the-art audio codec models.\"], \"citations\": [{\"paper_id\": \"2306.06546\", \"title\": \"Descript Audio Codec (DAC)\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"\\u91c7\\u7528\\u517644.1kHz\\u7248\\u672c\\u4f5c\\u4e3a\\u97f3\\u9891\\u7f16\\u89e3\\u7801\\u5668\\uff0c\\u66ff\\u4ee3EnCodec\\u4ee5\\u63d0\\u5347\\u4fdd\\u771f\\u5ea6\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MLS\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"4.5\\u4e07\\u5c0f\\u6