": \"g2p\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"\\u7528\\u4e8e\\u5c06\\u6587\\u672c\\u8f6c\\u5f55\\u8f6c\\u6362\\u4e3a\\u97f3\\u7d20\\u4ee5\\u8ba1\\u7b97\\u8bed\\u901f\\u7684\\u5e93\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Stable Beluga 2.5\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"\\u5927\\u8bed\\u8a00\\u6a21\\u578b\\uff0c\\u7528\\u4e8e\\u5c06\\u5173\\u952e\\u8bcd\\u7ec4\\u5408\\u8f6c\\u5316\\u4e3a\\u5b8c\\u6574\\u7684\\u81ea\\u7136\\u8bed\\u8a00\\u63cf\\u8ff0\\u53e5\\u5b50\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"DAC\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Descript Audio Codec 44.1kHz\\u7248\\u672c\\uff0c\\u4f5c\\u4e3a\\u6a21\\u578b\\u7684\\u97f3\\u9891\\u7f16\\u89e3\\u7801\\u5668\\u751f\\u6210\\u79bb\\u6563\\u6807\\u8bb0\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"EnCodec\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"\\u672a\\u91c7\\u7528\\u7684\\u5e38\\u7528\\u7f16\\u89e3\\u7801\\u5668\\uff0c\\u4f5c\\u8005\\u6307\\u51faDAC\\u5728\\u5176\\u5ba2\\u89c2\\u548c\\u4e3b\\u89c2\\u6307\\u6807\\u4e0a\\u4fdd\\u771f\\u5ea6\\u5747\\u9ad8\\u4e8eEnCodec\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"AudioCraft\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"\\u901a\\u7528\\u97f3\\u9891\\u751f\\u6210\\u5e93\\uff0c\\u672c\\u6587\\u57fa\\u4e8e\\u6b64\\u8fdb\\u884cTTS\\u67b6\\u6784\\u9002\\u914d\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Audiobox\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"\\u540c\\u671f\\u5de5\\u4f5c\\uff0c\\u4f5c\\u4e3a\\u57fa\\u7ebf\\u5728\\u5b9e\\u9a8c\\u4e2d\\u8fdb\\u884c\\u5bf9\\u6bd4\\u8bc4\\u4f30\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Torchaudio SQUIM\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"\\u63d0\\u4f9b\\u65e0\\u53c2\\u8003\\u4f30\\u8ba1\\u5ba2\\u89c2\\u97f3\\u9891\\u4fdd\\u771f\\u5ea6\\u6307\\u6807\\uff08PESQ, STOI, SI-SDR\\uff09\\u7684\\u6a21\\u578b\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Rainbow Passage\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"\\u53e3\\u97f3\\u6d4b\\u8bd5\\u96c6\\u7ed3\\u5408\\u4f7f\\u7528\\u7684\\u53e5\\u5b50\\u6765\\u6e90\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Comma Gets a Cure\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"\\u53e3\\u97f3\\u6d4b\\u8bd5\\u96c6\\u7ed3\\u5408\\u4f7f\\u7528\\u7684\\u53e5\\u5b50\\u6765\\u6e90\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Please Call Stella\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"\\u53e3\\u97f3\\u6d4b\\u8bd5\\u96c6\\u7ed3\\u5408\\u4f7f\\u7528\\u7684\\u53e5\\u5b50\\u6765\\u6e90\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}], \"code_url\": \"\", \"abstract\": \"Text-to-speech models trained on large-scale datasets have demonstrated impressive in-context learning capabilities and naturalness. However, control of speaker identity and style in these models typically requires conditioning on reference speech recordings, limiting creative applications. Alternatively, natural language prompting of speaker identity and style has demonstrated promising results and provides an intuitive method of control. However, reliance on human-labeled descriptions prevents scaling to large datasets. Our work bridges the gap between these two approaches. We propose a scalable method for labeling various aspects of speaker identity, style, and recording conditions. We then apply this method to a 45k hour dataset, which we use to train a speech language model. Furthermore, we propose simple methods for increasing audio fidelity, significantly outperforming recent work despite relying entirely on found data. Our results demonstrate high-fidelity speech generation in a diverse range of accents, prosodic styles, channel conditions, and acoustic conditions, all accomplished with a single model and intuitive natural language conditioning. Audio samples can be heard at https://text-description-to-speech.com/.\", \"status\": \"unread\", \"compile_status\": \"compiled\", \"compiled_at\": \"2026-04-27T03:52:27.695397\"}, \"score\": 2}, {\"paper\": {\"arxiv_id\": \"2604.18360\", \"title\": \"Omni-Embed-Audio: Leveraging Multimodal LLMs for Robust Audio-Text Retrieval\", \"authors\": [\"HaeJun Yoo\", \"Yongseop Shin\", \"Insung Lee\", \"Myoung-Wan Koo\", \"Du-Seong Chang\"], \"year\": 2026, \"venue\": \"\", \"categories\": [\"cs.SD\", \"cs.CL\"], \"topic\": \"audio_understanding\", \"tags\": [\"SSL\", \"SSL/\\u5bf9\\u6bd4\\u5f0f\", \"Eval\", \"Eval/\\u5d4c\\u5165\"], \"contributions\": [\"We present OEA, a unified encoder architecture leveraging multimodal LLMs that demonstrates dominant text-to-text retrieval performance and superior semantic understanding of complex queries.\", \"We identify query-type robustness as a critical dimension of audio retrieval evaluation and introduce the UIQ benchmark with five query types organized into three linguistically-motivated categories.\", \"We propose novel hard negative-based evaluation metrics (HNSR, TFR, \\u0394-Rank) that reveal limitations in standard retrieval metrics and demonstrate OEA's superior discrimination capabilities.\"], \"citations\": [{\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"WavCaps\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Training dataset with 275,618 filtered samples for initial alignment\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"AudioCaps v2\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Training dataset with 91,256 samples for title-based retrieval\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Clotho v2\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Optional training dataset with 3,839 clips to improve natural audio description performance\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Nemotron-3B\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Multimodal LLM backbone used for OEA-Nemo3B variants\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Qwen2.5-Omni-3B\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Multimodal LLM backbone used for OEA-Qwen3B variants\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Qwen2.5-Omni-7B\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Multimodal LLM backbone used for OEA-Qwen7B variants\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MGA-CLAP\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Used for acoustic candidate retrieval in the hard negative mining pipeline\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"BGE-large-en-v1.5\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Sentence embedding model used for semantic dissimilarity scoring in hard negative mining\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"GPT-5.1\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"LLM used for automated UIQ query generation\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"LAION-CLAP\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"CLAP variant baseline compared against in experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Robust-CLAP\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"CLAP variant baseline compared against in experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MGA-CLAP\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"CLAP variant baseline compared against in experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"M2D-CLAP\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Current SOTA CLAP baseline explicitly compared against in experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"AudioCaps\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Evaluation dataset with 975 clips and 5 captions per clip\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Clotho\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Evaluation dataset with 1,045 clips and 5 captions per clip\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MECAT\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Leak-free evaluation benchmark with 847 auto-captioned pairs from ACAV100M\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"AudioCaps-UIQ\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"UIQ evaluation benchmark dataset for diverse query types\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Clotho-UIQ\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"UIQ evaluation benchmark dataset for diverse query types\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MECAT-UIQ\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"UIQ evaluation benchmark dataset for diverse query types\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Claude Opus 4.5\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"LLM used to evaluate the quality and validity of generated UIQ queries\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}], \"code_url\": \"\", \"abstract\": \"Audio-text retrieval systems based on Contrastive Language-Audio Pretraining (CLAP) achieve strong performance on traditional benchmarks; however, these benchmarks rely on caption-style queries that differ substantially from real-world search behavior, limiting their assessment of practical retrieval robustness. We present Omni-Embed-Audio (OEA), a retrieval-oriented encoder leveraging multimodal LLMs with native audio understanding. To systematically evaluate robustness beyond caption-style queries, we introduce User-Intent Queries (UIQs) - five formulations reflecting natural search behaviors: questions, commands, keyword tags, paraphrases, and exclusion-based negative queries. For negative queries, we develop a hard negative mining pipeline and propose discrimination metrics (HNSR, TFR) assessing models' ability to suppress acoustically similar distractors. Experiments on AudioCaps, Clotho, and MECAT show that OEA achieves comparable text-to-audio retrieval performance to state-of-the-art M2D-CLAP, while demonstrating clear advantages in two critical areas: (1) dominant text-to-text retrieval (+22% relative improvement), and (2) substantially superior hard negative discrimination (+4.3%p HNSR@10, +34.7% relative TFR@10), revealing that LLM backbones provide superior semantic understanding of complex queries.\", \"status\": \"unread\", \"compile_status\": \"compiled\", \"compiled_at\": \"2026-04-28T06:12:34.037698\"}, \"score\": 2}, {\"paper\": {\"arxiv_id\": \"2106.06909\", \"title\": \"GigaSpeech: An Evolving, Multi-domain ASR Corpus with 10,000 Hours of Transcribed Audio\", \"authors\": [\"Guoguo Chen\", \"Shuzhou Chai\", \"Guanbo Wang\", \"Jiayu Du\", \"Wei-Qiang Zhang\", \"Chao Weng\", \"Dan Su\", \"Daniel Povey\", \"Jan Trmal\", \"Junbo Zhang\", \"Mingjie Jin\", \"Sanjeev Khudanpur\", \"Shinji Watanabe\", \"Shuaijiang Zhao\", \"Wei Zou\", \"Xiangang Li\", \"Xuchen Yao\", \"Yongqing Wang\", \"Yujun Wang\", \"Zhao You\", \"Zhiyong Yan\"], \"year\": 2021, \"venue\": \"\", \"categories\": [\"cs.SD\", \"cs.CL\", \"eess.AS\"], \"topic\": \"speech_dataset\", \"tags\": [\"ASR\"], \"contributions\": [\"Release of an evolving, multi-domain English speech recognition corpus with 10,000 hours of labeled audio.\", \"Provision of a scalable, reliable pipeline for generating speech recognition corpora.\"], \"citations\": [{\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"GigaSpeech\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"The primary dataset used for training and evaluation, providing 10,000 hours of labeled audio across multiple subsets.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Opus\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Audio codec used to compress the training data at 32 kbps with minimal WER degradation.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Athena\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Evaluated as a baseline ASR toolkit (encoder-decoder Transformer + CTC + RNNLM) on the GigaSpeech dataset.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"ESPnet\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Evaluated as a baseline ASR toolkit (Conformer + Transformer + CTC) on the GigaSpeech dataset.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Kaldi\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Evaluated as a baseline ASR toolkit (Chain model with LF-MMI) on the GigaSpeech dataset.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Pika\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Evaluated as a baseline ASR toolkit (CNN+Transformer RNN-T) on the GigaSpeech dataset.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"LibriSpeech\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Recommended as a supplementary evaluation set for the audiobook domain, ensuring no overlap with GigaSpeech.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Speechocean\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Professional human transcribers from Speechocean were used to process the DEV and TEST sets as ground truth for evaluation.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}], \"code_url\": \"\", \"abstract\": \"This paper introduces GigaSpeech, an evolving, multi-domain English speech recognition corpus with 10,000 hours of high quality labeled audio suitable for supervised training, and 40,000 hours of total audio suitable for semi-supervised and unsupervised training. Around 40,000 hours of transcribed audio is first collected from audiobooks, podcasts and YouTube, covering both read and spontaneous speaking styles, and a variety of topics, such as arts, science, sports, etc. A new forced alignment and segmentation pipeline is proposed to create sentence segments suitable for speech recognition training, and to filter out segments with low-quality transcription. For system training, GigaSpeech provides five subsets of different sizes, 10h, 250h, 1000h, 2500h, and 10000h. For our 10,000-hour XL training subset, we cap the word error rate at 4% during the filtering/validation stage, and for all our other smaller training subsets, we cap it at 0%. The DEV and TEST evaluation sets, on the other hand, are re-processed by professional human transcribers to ensure high transcription quality. Baseline systems are provided for popular speech recognition toolkits, namely Athena, ESPnet, Kaldi and Pika.\", \"status\": \"unread\", \"compile_status\": \"compiled\", \"compiled_at\": \"2026-04-27T03:25:25.118147\"}, \"score\": 2}, {\"paper\": {\"arxiv_id\": \"2411.01156\", \"title\": \"Fish-Speech: Leveraging Large Language Models for Advanced Multilingual Text-to-Speech Synthesis\", \"authors\": [\"Shijia Liao\", \"Yuxuan Wang\", \"Tianyu Li\", \"Yifan Cheng\", \"Ruoyi Zhang\", \"Rongzhi Zhou\", \"Yijin Xing\"], \"year\": 2024, \"venue\": \"\", \"categories\": [\"cs.SD\", \"eess.AS\"], \"topic\": \"tts_vc\", \"tags\": [\"TTS\", \"\\u538b\\u7f29\", \"TTS/\\u67b6\\u6784-AR-LLM\", \"TTS/\\u529f\\u80fd-\\u591a\\u8bed\\u8a00\", \"TTS/\\u529f\\u80fd-\\u6d41\\u5f0f\", \"\\u538b\\u7f29/\\u91cf\\u5316-FSQ\"], \"contributions\": [\"We introduce Fish-Speech, a novel TTS framework that leverages LLMs and a Dual-AR architecture to replace traditional G2P conversion, providing robust and scalable multilingual speech synthesis.\", \"We present FFGAN, an advanced vocoder that integrates multiple vector quantization techniques to achieve high-fidelity speech synthesis with optimized compression ratios and codebook utilization.\", \"We develop fish-tech acceleration methodologies, enabling the system to achieve real-time factors of approximately 1:5 on consumer-grade NVIDIA RTX 4060 mobile platforms and 1:15 on high-performance NVIDIA RTX 4090 configurations with a latency of 150ms.\"], \"citations\": [{\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"CosyVoice\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Baseline model based on flow matching compared against in experiments.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"F5-TTS\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Baseline model compared against in experiments.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Reecho\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Baseline model compared against in experiments.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Whisper-medium\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"ASR model used to compute WER for intelligibility evaluation.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Resemblyzer\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Framework used to compute Speaker Embedding Similarity.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"SpeechBrain\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Framework (v1.0.1) used to compute Speaker Embedding Similarity.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"EVA-GAN\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"FF-GAN is improved based on the EVA-GAN architecture.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}], \"code_url\": \"\", \"abstract\": \"Text-to-Speech (TTS) systems face ongoing challenges in processing complex linguistic features, handling polyphonic expressions, and producing natural-sounding multilingual speech - capabilities that are crucial for future AI applications. In this paper, we present Fish-Speech, a novel framework that implements a serial fast-slow Dual Autoregressive (Dual-AR) architecture to enhance the stability of Grouped Finite Scalar Vector Quantization (GFSQ) in sequence generation tasks. This architecture improves codebook processing efficiency while maintaining high-fidelity outputs, making it particularly effective for AI interactions and voice cloning.   Fish-Speech leverages Large Language Models (LLMs) for linguistic feature extraction, eliminating the need for traditional grapheme-to-phoneme (G2P) conversion and thereby streamlining the synthesis pipeline and enhancing multilingual support. Additionally, we developed FF-GAN through GFSQ to achieve superior compression ratios and near 100\\\\% codebook utilization.   Our approach addresses key limitations of current TTS systems while providing a foundation for more sophisticated, context-aware speech synthesis. Experimental results show that Fish-Speech significantly outperforms baseline models in handling complex linguistic scenarios and voice cloning tasks, demonstrating its potential to advance TTS technology in AI applications. The implementation is open source at \\\\href{https://github.com/fishaudio/fish-speech}{https://github.com/fishaudio/fish-speech}.\", \"status\": \"unread\", \"compile_status\": \"compiled\", \"compiled_at\": \"2026-04-27T04:16:25.471384\"}, \"score\": 2}]", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "1446fd4a-9a9a-4b2f-bacb-2deecf7d52d8", "uuid": "18bb816b-a522-4493-ad5e-9ee2ea4c6f0b", "timestamp": "2026-07-14T14:22:36.971Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "[]\n===\n[]\n===\n[{\"paper\": {\"arxiv_id\": \"2509.09174\", \"title\": \"EchoX: Towards Mitigating Acoustic-Semantic Gap via Echo Training for Speech-to-Speech LLMs\", \"authors\": [\"Yuhao Zhang\", \"Yuhao Du\", \"Zhanchen Dai\", \"Xiangnan Ma\", \"Kaiqi Kou\", \"Benyou Wang\", \"Haizhou Li\"], \"year\": 2025, \"venue\": \"\", \"categories\": [\"cs.CL\", \"cs.AI\", \"cs.SD\"], \"topic\": \"audio_understanding\", \"tags\": [\"LALM\", \"LALM/\\u5bf9\\u8bdd\\u578b\", \"LALM/\\u97f3\\u9891\\u6807\\u8bb0-\\u878d\\u5408\", \"TTS\"], \"contributions\": [\"Identification of the acoustic-semantic gap as a primary cause of intelligence degradation in speech-to-speech large language models.\", \"Proposal of EchoX, a framework that uses an auxiliary Echo decoder to dynamically generate speech training targets based on semantic understanding.\", \"Introduction of a three-stage training pipeline consisting of speech-to-text training, text-to-codec training, and echo training to bridge the acoustic-semantic gap.\", \"Design of a denoising adapter combined with a cosine similarity loss to align hidden representations with text embeddings and minimize noise during speech token generation.\", \"Adoption of unit language to construct speech tokens that significantly compress speech sequences while maintaining synthesis quality.\", \"Development of a streaming inference mechanism based on a trigger feature to enable real-time generation and mitigate long-sequence generation difficulties.\", \"Demonstration of advanced performance on knowledge-based QA benchmarks using approximately six thousand hours of training data, achieving results comparable to models trained on millions of hours.\"], \"citations\": [{\"paper_id\": \"2409.00750\", \"title\": \"LibriSpeech\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"ASR dataset used for training the S2T module.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"HuBERT\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Used to extract continuous representations from the 11th hidden layer for unit extraction\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Soundwave\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Used as the audio encoding and adaptation architecture for the S2T LLM\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"LLaMA 3.2\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Base text LLM used for the 3B model\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"LLaMA 3.1\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Base text LLM used for the 8B model\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MLS\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Subset used as ASR training data (723k utterances, 3000 hours)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"AudioQA-1M\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"TTS training data (178k utterances, 989 hours, text only used)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"SpeechInstruct\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"TTS training data (31k utterances, 84 hours)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"HH-RLHF-Speech\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"TTS training data (124k utterances, 656 hours, converted from text)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"sharechatx\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"SQA training data (43k utterances, 178 hours)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Magpie-Pro-Speech+\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"SQA training data (117k utterances, 327 hours)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Google TTS\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Used in the data cleaning pipeline to synthesize speech\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"GPT-SoVITS\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Used in the data cleaning pipeline to synthesize speech\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Llama Questions\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Knowledge QA benchmark for evaluating semantic and knowledge reasoning ability\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Web Questions\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Knowledge QA benchmark for evaluating semantic and knowledge reasoning ability\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"TriviaQA\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Knowledge QA benchmark for evaluating semantic and knowledge reasoning ability\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"UTMOS\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Metric for evaluating the acoustic quality of generated speech\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"AlpacaEval\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Dataset used for human evaluation of speech interaction\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"OmniDRCA(2B)\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Evaluated 3B-level baseline model\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"LLaMA-Omni2-3B\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Evaluated 3B-level baseline model\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"GPT-4o-Realtime\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Evaluated 8B+ level baseline model\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"VITA-Audio\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Evaluated 8B+ level baseline model\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MinMo\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Evaluated 8B+ level baseline model\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MiniCPM-o 2.6\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Evaluated 8B+ level baseline model\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"OmniDRCA(8B)\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Evaluated 8B+ level baseline model\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"GLM-4-Voice\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Evaluated 8B+ level baseline model\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"LLaMA-Omni2-7B\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Evaluated 8B+ level baseline model\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Freeze-Omni\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Evaluated 8B+ level baseline model and human evaluation comparison target\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Moshi\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Evaluated 8B+ level baseline model\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}], \"code_url\": \"\", \"abstract\": \"Speech-to-speech large language models (SLLMs) are attracting increasing attention. Derived from text-based large language models (LLMs), SLLMs often exhibit degradation in knowledge and reasoning capabilities. We hypothesize that this limitation arises because current training paradigms for SLLMs fail to bridge the acoustic-semantic gap in the feature representation space. To address this issue, we propose EchoX, which leverages semantic representations and dynamically generates speech training targets. This approach integrates both acoustic and semantic learning, enabling EchoX to preserve strong reasoning abilities as a speech LLM. Experimental results demonstrate that EchoX, with about six thousand hours of training data, achieves advanced performance on multiple knowledge-based question-answering benchmarks. The project is available at https://github.com/FreedomIntelligence/EchoX.\", \"status\": \"unread\", \"compile_status\": \"compiled\", \"compiled_at\": \"2026-04-27T05:29:25.143825\"}, \"score\": 31}, {\"paper\": {\"arxiv_id\": \"2402.01912\", \"title\": \"Natural language guidance of high-fidelity text-to-speech with synthetic annotations\", \"authors\": [\"Dan Lyth\", \"Simon King\"], \"year\": 2024, \"venue\": \"\", \"categories\": [\"cs.SD\", \"cs.CL\", \"eess.AS\"], \"topic\": \"tts_vc\", \"tags\": [\"TTS\", \"TTS/\\u67b6\\u6784-AR-LLM\", \"TTS/\\u63a7\\u5236-NL\\u63cf\\u8ff0\", \"TTS/\\u529f\\u80fd-\\u591a\\u8bf4\\u8bdd\\u4eba\"], \"contributions\": [\"Proposed a scalable method for automatically labeling large speech datasets with multiple attributes including gender, accent, speaking rate, pitch, and recording conditions.\", \"Trained a speech language model on a 45k hour automatically-labeled dataset to independently control various speech attributes and create unseen speaker identity and style combinations via natural language.\", \"Demonstrated that high-fidelity audio generation can be achieved by training on a dataset with as little as 1% high-quality audio combined with state-of-the-art audio codec models.\"], \"citations\": [{\"paper_id\": \"2306.06546\", \"title\": \"Descript Audio Codec (DAC)\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"\\u91c7\\u7528\\u517644.1kHz\\u7248\\u672c\\u4f5c\\u4e3a\\u97f3\\u9891\\u7f16\\u89e3\\u7801\\u5668\\uff0c\\u66ff\\u4ee3EnCodec\\u4ee5\\u63d0\\u5347\\u4fdd\\u771f\\u5ea6\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MLS\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"4.5\\u4e07\\u5c0f\\u65f6\\u5927\\u89c4\\u6a21\\u8bed\\u97f3\\u6570\\u636e\\u96c6\\uff0c\\u7528\\u4e8e\\u6a21\\u578b\\u8bad\\u7ec3\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"LibriTTS-R\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"585\\u5c0f\\u65f6\\u7ecf\\u589e\\u5f3a\\u7684\\u9ad8\\u4fdd\\u771f\\u8bed\\u97f3\\u6570\\u636e\\u96c6\\uff0c\\u7528\\u4e8e\\u6a21\\u578b\\u8bad\\u7ec3\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"EdAcc\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"\\u53e3\\u97f3\\u5206\\u7c7b\\u5668\\u7684\\u8bad\\u7ec3\\u6570\\u636e\\u6e90\\u4e4b\\u4e00\\uff0c\\u8986\\u76d653\\u79cd\\u53e3\\u97f3\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"VCTK\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"\\u53e3\\u97f3\\u5206\\u7c7b\\u5668\\u7684\\u8bad\\u7ec3\\u6570\\u636e\\u6e90\\u4e4b\\u4e00\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"VoxPopuli\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"\\u53e3\\u97f3\\u5206\\u7c7b\\u5668\\u7684\\u8bad\\u7ec3\\u6570\\u636e\\u6e90\\u82f1\\u8bed\\u53e3\\u97f3\\u5b50\\u96c6\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Miipher\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"\\u7528\\u4e8e\\u589e\\u5f3aLibriTTS-R\\u6570\\u636e\\u96c6\\u4ee5\\u83b7\\u5f97\\u9ad8\\u4fdd\\u771f\\u97f3\\u9891\\u7684\\u7cfb\\u7edf\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Brouhaha\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"\\u7528\\u4e8e\\u63d0\\u53d6\\u5f55\\u97f3\\u8d28\\u91cf\\u4ee3\\u7406\\u6307\\u6807\\uff08SNR\\u548cC50\\uff09\\u7684\\u5e93\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"PENN\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"\\u7528\\u4e8e\\u8ba1\\u7b97\\u6240\\u6709\\u8bdd\\u8bed\\u97f3\\u9ad8\\u8f6e\\u5ed3\\u7684\\u5e93\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"g2p\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"\\u7528\\u4e8e\\u5c06\\u6587\\u672c\\u8f6c\\u5f55\\u8f6c\\u6362\\u4e3a\\u97f3\\u7d20\\u4ee5\\u8ba1\\u7b97\\u8bed\\u901f\\u7684\\u5e93\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Stable Beluga 2.5\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"\\u5927\\u8bed\\u8a00\\u6a21\\u578b\\uff0c\\u7528\\u4e8e\\u5c06\\u5173\\u952e\\u8bcd\\u7ec4\\u5408\\u8f6c\\u5316\\u4e3a\\u5b8c\\u6574\\u7684\\u81ea\\u7136\\u8bed\\u8a00\\u63cf\\u8ff0\\u53e5\\u5b50\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"DAC\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Descript Audio Codec 44.1kHz\\u7248\\u672c\\uff0c\\u4f5c\\u4e3a\\u6a21\\u578b\\u7684\\u97f3\\u9891\\u7f16\\u89e3\\u7801\\u5668\\u751f\\u6210\\u79bb\\u6563\\u6807\\u8bb0\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"EnCodec\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"\\u672a\\u91c7\\u7528\\u7684\\u5e38\\u7528\\u7f16\\u89e3\\u7801\\u5668\\uff0c\\u4f5c\\u8005\\u6307\\u51faDAC\\u5728\\u5176\\u5ba2\\u89c2\\u548c\\u4e3b\\u89c2\\u6307\\u6807\\u4e0a\\u4fdd\\u771f\\u5ea6\\u5747\\u9ad8\\u4e8eEnCodec\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"AudioCraft\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"\\u901a\\u7528\\u97f3\\u9891\\u751f\\u6210\\u5e93\\uff0c\\u672c\\u6587\\u57fa\\u4e8e\\u6b64\\u8fdb\\u884cTTS\\u67b6\\u6784\\u9002\\u914d\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Audiobox\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"\\u540c\\u671f\\u5de5\\u4f5c\\uff0c\\u4f5c\\u4e3a\\u57fa\\u7ebf\\u5728\\u5b9e\\u9a8c\\u4e2d\\u8fdb\\u884c\\u5bf9\\u6bd4\\u8bc4\\u4f30\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Torchaudio SQUIM\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"\\u63d0\\u4f9b\\u65e0\\u53c2\\u8003\\u4f30\\u8ba1\\u5ba2\\u89c2\\u97f3\\u9891\\u4fdd\\u771f\\u5ea6\\u6307\\u6807\\uff08PESQ, STOI, SI-SDR\\uff09\\u7684\\u6a21\\u578b\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Rainbow Passage\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"\\u53e3\\u97f3\\u6d4b\\u8bd5\\u96c6\\u7ed3\\u5408\\u4f7f\\u7528\\u7684\\u53e5\\u5b50\\u6765\\u6e90\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Comma Gets a Cure\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"\\u53e3\\u97f3\\u6d4b\\u8bd5\\u96c6\\u7ed3\\u5408\\u4f7f\\u7528\\u7684\\u53e5\\u5b50\\u6765\\u6e90\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Please Call Stella\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"\\u53e3\\u97f3\\u6d4b\\u8bd5\\u96c6\\u7ed3\\u5408\\u4f7f\\u7528\\u7684\\u53e5\\u5b50\\u6765\\u6e90\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}], \"code_url\": \"\", \"abstract\": \"Text-to-speech models trained on large-scale datasets have demonstrated impressive in-context learning capabilities and naturalness. However, control of speaker identity and style in these models typically requires conditioning on reference speech recordings, limiting creative applications. Alternatively, natural language prompting of speaker identity and style has demonstrated promising results and provides an intuitive method of control. However, reliance on human-labeled descriptions prevents scaling to large datasets. Our work bridges the gap between these two approaches. We propose a scalable method for labeling various aspects of speaker identity, style, and recording conditions. We then apply this method to a 45k hour dataset, which we use to train a speech language model. Furthermore, we propose simple methods for increasing audio fidelity, significantly outperforming recent work despite relying entirely on found data. Our results demonstrate high-fidelity speech generation in a diverse range of accents, prosodic styles, channel conditions, and acoustic conditions, all accomplished with a single model and intuitive natural language conditioning. Audio samples can be heard at https://text-description-to-speech.com/.\", \"status\": \"unread\", \"compile_status\": \"compiled\", \"compiled_at\": \"2026-04-27T03:52:27.695397\"}, \"score\": 2}, {\"paper\": {\"arxiv_id\": \"2604.18360\", \"title\": \"Omni-Embed-Audio: Leveraging Multimodal LLMs for Robust Audio-Text Retrieval\", \"authors\": [\"HaeJun Yoo\", \"Yongseop Shin\", \"Insung Lee\", \"Myoung-Wan Koo\", \"Du-Seong Chang\"], \"year\": 2026, \"venue\": \"\", \"categories\": [\"cs.SD\", \"cs.CL\"], \"topic\": \"audio_understanding\", \"tags\": [\"SSL\", \"SSL/\\u5bf9\\u6bd4\\u5f0f\", \"Eval\", \"Eval/\\u5d4c\\u5165\"], \"contributions\": [\"We present OEA, a unified encoder architecture leveraging multimodal LLMs that demonstrates dominant text-to-text retrieval performance and superior semantic understanding of complex queries.\", \"We identify query-type robustness as a critical dimension of audio retrieval evaluation and introduce the UIQ benchmark with five query types organized into three linguistically-motivated categories.\", \"We propose novel hard negative-based evaluation metrics (HNSR, TFR, \\u0394-Rank) that reveal limitations in standard retrieval metrics and demonstrate OEA's superior discrimination capabilities.\"], \"citations\": [{\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"WavCaps\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Training dataset with 275,618 filtered samples for initial alignment\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"AudioCaps v2\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Training dataset with 91,256 samples for title-based retrieval\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Clotho v2\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Optional training dataset with 3,839 clips to improve natural audio description performance\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Nemotron-3B\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Multimodal LLM backbone used for OEA-Nemo3B variants\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Qwen2.5-Omni-3B\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Multimodal LLM backbone used for OEA-Qwen3B variants\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Qwen2.5-Omni-7B\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Multimodal LLM backbone used for OEA-Qwen7B variants\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MGA-CLAP\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Used for acoustic candidate retrieval in the hard negative mining pipeline\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"BGE-large-en-v1.5\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Sentence embedding model used for semantic dissimilarity scoring in hard negative mining\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"GPT-5.1\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"LLM used for automated UIQ query generation\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"LAION-CLAP\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"CLAP variant baseline compared against in experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Robust-CLAP\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"CLAP variant baseline compared against in experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MGA-CLAP\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"CLAP variant baseline compared against in experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"M2D-CLAP\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Current SOTA CLAP baseline explicitly compared against in experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"AudioCaps\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Evaluation dataset with 975 clips and 5 captions per clip\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Clotho\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Evaluation dataset with 1,045 clips and 5 captions per clip\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MECAT\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Leak-free evaluation benchmark with 847 auto-captioned pairs from ACAV100M\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"AudioCaps-UIQ\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"UIQ evaluation benchmark dataset for diverse query types\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Clotho-UIQ\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"UIQ evaluation benchmark dataset for diverse query types\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MECAT-UIQ\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"UIQ evaluation benchmark dataset for diverse query types\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Claude Opus 4.5\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"LLM used to evaluate the quality and validity of generated UIQ queries\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}], \"code_url\": \"\", \"abstract\": \"Audio-text retrieval systems based on Contrastive Language-Audio Pretraining (CLAP) achieve strong performance on traditional benchmarks; however, these benchmarks rely on caption-style queries that differ substantially from real-world search behavior, limiting their assessment of practical retrieval robustness. We present Omni-Embed-Audio (OEA), a retrieval-oriented encoder leveraging multimodal LLMs with native audio understanding. To systematically evaluate robustness beyond caption-style queries, we introduce User-Intent Queries (UIQs) - five formulations reflecting natural search behaviors: questions, commands, keyword tags, paraphrases, and exclusion-based negative queries. For negative queries, we develop a hard negative mining pipeline and propose discrimination metrics (HNSR, TFR) assessing models' ability to suppress acoustically similar distractors. Experiments on AudioCaps, Clotho, and MECAT show that OEA achieves comparable text-to-audio retrieval performance to state-of-the-art M2D-CLAP, while demonstrating clear advantages in two critical areas: (1) dominant text-to-text retrieval (+22% relative improvement), and (2) substantially superior hard negative discrimination (+4.3%p HNSR@10, +34.7% relative TFR@10), revealing that LLM backbones provide superior semantic understanding of complex queries.\", \"status\": \"unread\", \"compile_status\": \"compiled\", \"compiled_at\": \"2026-04-28T06:12:34.037698\"}, \"score\": 2}, {\"paper\": {\"arxiv_id\": \"2106.06909\", \"title\": \"GigaSpeech: An Evolving, Multi-domain ASR Corpus with 10,000 Hours of Transcribed Audio\", \"authors\": [\"Guoguo Chen\", \"Shuzhou Chai\", \"Guanbo Wang\", \"Jiayu Du\", \"Wei-Qiang Zhang\", \"Chao Weng\", \"Dan Su\", \"Daniel Povey\", \"Jan Trmal\", \"Junbo Zhang\", \"Mingjie Jin\", \"Sanjeev Khudanpur\", \"Shinji Watanabe\", \"Shuaijiang Zhao\", \"Wei Zou\", \"Xiangang Li\", \"Xuchen Yao\", \"Yongqing Wang\", \"Yujun Wang\", \"Zhao You\", \"Zhiyong Yan\"], \"year\": 2021, \"venue\": \"\", \"categories\": [\"cs.SD\", \"cs.CL\", \"eess.AS\"], \"topic\": \"speech_dataset\", \"tags\": [\"ASR\"], \"contributions\": [\"Release of an evolving, multi-domain English speech recognition corpus with 10,000 hours of labeled audio.\", \"Provision of a scalable, reliable pipeline for generating speech recognition corpora.\"], \"citations\": [{\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"GigaSpeech\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"The primary dataset used for training and evaluation, providing 10,000 hours of labeled audio across multiple subsets.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Opus\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Audio codec used to compress the training data at 32 kbps with minimal WER degradation.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Athena\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Evaluated as a baseline ASR toolkit (encoder-decoder Transformer + CTC + RNNLM) on the GigaSpeech dataset.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"ESPnet\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Evaluated as a baseline ASR toolkit (Conformer + Transformer + CTC) on the GigaSpeech dataset.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Kaldi\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Evaluated as a baseline ASR toolkit (Chain model with LF-MMI) on the GigaSpeech dataset.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Pika\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Evaluated as a baseline ASR toolkit (CNN+Transformer RNN-T) on the GigaSpeech dataset.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"LibriSpeech\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Recommended as a supplementary evaluation set for the audiobook domain, ensuring no overlap with GigaSpeech.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Speechocean\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Professional human transcribers from Speechocean were used to process the DEV and TEST sets as ground truth for evaluation.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}], \"code_url\": \"\", \"abstract\": \"This paper introduces GigaSpeech, an evolving, multi-domain English speech recognition corpus with 10,000 hours of high quality labeled audio suitable for supervised training, and 40,000 hours of total audio suitable for semi-supervised and unsupervised training. Around 40,000 hours of transcribed audio is first collected from audiobooks, podcasts and YouTube, covering both read and spontaneous speaking styles, and a variety of topics, such as arts, science, sports, etc. A new forced alignment and segmentation pipeline is proposed to create sentence segments suitable for speech recognition training, and to filter out segments with low-quality transcription. For system training, GigaSpeech provides five subsets of different sizes, 10h, 250h, 1000h, 2500h, and 10000h. For our 10,000-hour XL training subset, we cap the word error rate at 4% during the filtering/validation stage, and for all our other smaller training subsets, we cap it at 0%. The DEV and TEST evaluation sets, on the other hand, are re-processed by professional human transcribers to ensure high transcription quality. Baseline systems are provided for popular speech recognition toolkits, namely Athena, ESPnet, Kaldi and Pika.\", \"status\": \"unread\", \"compile_status\": \"compiled\", \"compiled_at\": \"2026-04-27T03:25:25.118147\"}, \"score\": 2}, {\"paper\": {\"arxiv_id\": \"2411.01156\", \"title\": \"Fish-Speech: Leveraging Large Language Models for Advanced Multilingual Text-to-Speech Synthesis\", \"authors\": [\"Shijia Liao\", \"Yuxuan Wang\", \"Tianyu Li\", \"Yifan Cheng\", \"Ruoyi Zhang\", \"Rongzhi Zhou\", \"Yijin Xing\"], \"year\": 2024, \"venue\": \"\", \"categories\": [\"cs.SD\", \"eess.AS\"], \"topic\": \"tts_vc\", \"tags\": [\"TTS\", \"\\u538b\\u7f29\", \"TTS/\\u67b6\\u6784-AR-LLM\", \"TTS/\\u529f\\u80fd-\\u591a\\u8bed\\u8a00\", \"TTS/\\u529f\\u80fd-\\u6d41\\u5f0f\", \"\\u538b\\u7f29/\\u91cf\\u5316-FSQ\"], \"contributions\": [\"We introduce Fish-Speech, a novel TTS framework that leverages LLMs and a Dual-AR architecture to replace traditional G2P conversion, providing robust and scalable multilingual speech synthesis.\", \"We present FFGAN, an advanced vocoder that integrates multiple vector quantization techniques to achieve high-fidelity speech synthesis with optimized compression ratios and codebook utilization.\", \"We develop fish-tech acceleration methodologies, enabling the system to achieve real-time factors of approximately 1:5 on consumer-grade NVIDIA RTX 4060 mobile platforms and 1:15 on high-performance NVIDIA RTX 4090 configurations with a latency of 150ms.\"], \"citations\": [{\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"CosyVoice\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Baseline model based on flow matching compared against in experiments.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"F5-TTS\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Baseline model compared against in experiments.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Reecho\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Baseline model compared against in experiments.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Whisper-medium\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"ASR model used to compute WER for intelligibility evaluation.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Resemblyzer\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Framework used to compute Speaker Embedding Similarity.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"SpeechBrain\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Framework (v1.0.1) used to compute Speaker Embedding Similarity.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"EVA-GAN\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"FF-GAN is improved based on the EVA-GAN architecture.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}], \"code_url\": \"\", \"abstract\": \"Text-to-Speech (TTS) systems face ongoing challenges in processing complex linguistic features, handling polyphonic expressions, and producing natural-sounding multilingual speech - capabilities that are crucial for future AI applications. In this paper, we present Fish-Speech, a novel framework that implements a serial fast-slow Dual Autoregressive (Dual-AR) architecture to enhance the stability of Grouped Finite Scalar Vector Quantization (GFSQ) in sequence generation tasks. This architecture improves codebook processing efficiency while maintaining high-fidelity outputs, making it particularly effective for AI interactions and voice cloning.   Fish-Speech leverages Large Language Models (LLMs) for linguistic feature extraction, eliminating the need for traditional grapheme-to-phoneme (G2P) conversion and thereby streamlining the synthesis pipeline and enhancing multilingual support. Additionally, we developed FF-GAN through GFSQ to achieve superior compression ratios and near 100\\\\% codebook utilization.   Our approach addresses key limitations of current TTS systems while providing a foundation for more sophisticated, context-aware speech synthesis. Experimental results show that Fish-Speech significantly outperforms baseline models in handling complex linguistic scenarios and voice cloning tasks, demonstrating its potential to advance TTS technology in AI applications. The implementation is open source at \\\\href{https://github.com/fishaudio/fish-speech}{https://github.com/fishaudio/fish-speech}.\", \"status\": \"unread\", \"compile_status\": \"compiled\", \"compiled_at\": \"2026-04-27T04:16:25.471384\"}, \"score\": 2}]", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
